verbose_text: Moreover, in agreement with the notion that the ability of SGK3 to be inhibited by VPS34-IN1 is dependent on its PtdIns (3) P binding PX domain, we observed that VPS34-IN1 did not inhibit the activity of SGK2 isoform that does not possess a PX domain (XREF_FIG C).
evidence: VPS34-IN1 did not inhibit the activity of SGK2
